  "prompt": "What are Top 10 worst black Friday disasters?",
  "response": "Black Friday, known for its massive sales and crowds, has unfortunately been the site of numerous disasters over the years. Here are ten of the worst incidents associated with Black Friday shopping:\n\n1. **2008 Walmart Stampede (Valley Stream, New York)**: A 34-year-old man was tragically killed when a crowd of shoppers surged through the doors of a Walmart, pushing him to the ground. Several others were injured in the chaos.\n\n2. **2014 Grand Rapids Shooting (Michigan)**: A shooting occurred in a shopping plaza, with reports of at least one person injured during a Black Friday sale, prompting widespread panic among shoppers.\n\n3. **2005 Long Island Mall (New York)**: A large crowd waiting for a store\u2019s opening pushed through the doors when they opened, resulting in a stampede that injured several shoppers, including a pregnant woman.\n\n4. **2012 Black Friday Riot (Massachusetts)**: A violent altercation broke out in a Walmart over discounted items, leading to chaos and multiple injuries as shoppers fought over merchandise.\n\n5. **2011 Walmart Black Friday Incident (California)**: A woman used pepper spray on other shoppers to get to discounted goods during a sale, resulting in injuries to multiple people and evacuation of the store.\n\n6. **2006 Santa Monica Mall Shooting (California)**: During Black Friday sales, a shooting occurred at a mall, with one person injured. This raised concerns about safety during post-Thanksgiving sales.\n\n7. **2017 Target Shooting Incident (Duluth, Minnesota)**: An armed suspect entered a Target store during Black Friday sales, resulting in a lockdown and panic among shoppers until the suspect was apprehended.\n\n8. **2010 Black Friday Riot (Washington)**: A fight broke out among shoppers at a Best Buy store over narrow inventory, with several injuries reported amid the disorder.\n\n9. **2019 Best Buy Brawl (St. Paul, Minnesota)**: A large fight erupted at a Best Buy over limited stock, resulting in injuries as shoppers attempted to grab discounted electronics.\n\n10. **2003 Kmart Stampede (New York)**: Shoppers rushed through the doors of a Kmart when it opened, leading to near-stampede conditions and a number of injuries as people scrambled for discounted items.\n\nThese incidents illustrate the potential dangers associated with large crowds and the frenzy often seen during Black Friday sales. Retailers and law enforcement have since taken measures to improve safety during these events.",
